## 4. CSS `min-height` / `min-width` Rules -- App.css

These ensure flex children can shrink properly (needed for resize to work correctly):

| Line | Selector | Rule | Purpose |
|------|----------|------|---------|
| 164 | `.messages` | `min-height: 0` | Allows messages area to shrink when input area grows |
| 347 | `.input-bar` | `min-height: 0` | Allows input bar to shrink |
| 364 | `.input-box` | `min-height: 36px` | Minimum height of the `<textarea>` itself |
| 508 | `.modal-body` | `min-height: 0` | Allows modal body to shrink |
| 673 | `.status-body` | `min-height: 0` | Allows status panel body to shrink |
| 731 | `.activity-panel-wrap` | `min-height: 0` | Allows activity panel wrapper to shrink |
| 734 | `.activity-panel-wrap` | `min-width: 280px` | **Matches JS clamp of 280px** -- CSS-level min-width |
| 742 | `.activity-panel` | `min-height: 0` | Allows activity panel to shrink |
| 766 | `.activity-list` | `min-height: 0` | Allows activity list to shrink |

The `min-width: 280px` on `.activity-panel-wrap` (line 734) is the CSS-level counterpart to the JS clamp of `Math.max(280, ...)`. However, note that the input area's `Math.max(80, ...)` in JS does **not** have a corresponding CSS `min-height` on `.input-area` or its wrapper. The `.input-box` textarea has `min-height: 36px` (line 364), but that applies to the textarea's internal height, not the container.

